101
00:09:05,443 --> 00:09:06,844
I just need to look
around for a second.

102
00:09:06,912 --> 00:09:09,346
You have to pay the $5.

103
00:09:09,414 --> 00:09:10,615
Look, I'll stand
at the door.

104
00:09:10,682 --> 00:09:12,050
I won't even go inside.

105
00:09:12,117 --> 00:09:14,268
I just need to see
if my husband's in there.

106
00:09:14,569 --> 00:09:16,537
You have to pay
the admission.

107
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:21,926
He's gambling away
the money for our house.

108
00:09:23,328 --> 00:09:26,297
What does he look like?

109
00:09:26,364 --> 00:09:29,834
Long, brown hair.
Tall. Skinny.

110
00:09:30,352 --> 00:09:31,469
Ponytail.

111
00:09:31,537 --> 00:09:32,737
No. He's not in there.

112
00:09:34,673 --> 00:09:35,740
Can I just look?

113
00:09:35,808 --> 00:09:38,709
Lady, I just told you,
he's not in there.

114
00:09:54,860 --> 00:09:56,193
Hey!

115
00:09:56,261 --> 00:09:58,997
Hey! Hello! Hey!

116
00:10:37,536 --> 00:10:39,052
That's my car.

117
00:10:42,391 --> 00:10:43,908
What are you doing
with my car?

118
00:10:43,975 --> 00:10:45,943
That? I found it.

119
00:10:46,011 --> 00:10:47,945
You stole it?
- Had the keys in it.

120
00:10:48,013 --> 00:10:50,248
And so you just took it?

121
00:10:53,668 --> 00:10:56,086
We'll see what the troopers
have to say about that!

122
00:10:56,154 --> 00:10:58,239
Go ahead. They got
no jurisdiction here.

123
00:10:58,307 --> 00:11:00,274
This is Mohawk territory.

124
00:11:03,662 --> 00:11:04,778
Troy?

125
00:11:05,864 --> 00:11:07,264
You in there?

126
00:11:09,234 --> 00:11:12,086
If you are,
you better come out.

127
00:11:12,153 --> 00:11:14,355
Versailles says that if we get
the money to him by Christmas,

128
00:11:14,422 --> 00:11:16,290
we won't lose our deposit.

129
00:11:16,358 --> 00:11:18,242
I think we need
to talk about this, Troy.

130
00:11:18,310 --> 00:11:19,977
Come on out.

131
00:11:21,079 --> 00:11:22,313
Troy?

132
00:11:23,382 --> 00:11:24,682
(GUN FIRES)

133
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:28,552
I mean it, honey.
Come on out.

134
00:11:33,675 --> 00:11:38,095
The Tribal Police don't like people
shooting holes in other people's houses.

135
00:11:38,163 --> 00:11:42,316
This is New York State, so quit the
bullshit and give me my goddamn keys!

136
00:12:10,312 --> 00:12:12,847
LILA: This camper belongs
to my brother-in-law.

137
00:12:12,915 --> 00:12:14,231
He won't like this.

138
00:12:14,299 --> 00:12:15,999
Then you should
quit stealing cars.

139
00:12:16,067 --> 00:12:17,768
I thought
it was abandoned.

140
00:12:17,836 --> 00:12:20,204
The guy driving it
got on a bus.

141
00:12:20,272 --> 00:12:22,907
A bus? To where?

142
00:12:22,975 --> 00:12:26,327
New York. Buffalo.
I'm not sure.

143
00:12:27,612 --> 00:12:28,980
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

144
00:12:32,451 --> 00:12:35,319
Hello? Yeah, what is it?

145
00:12:35,387 --> 00:12:38,305
Well, there's a hard-boiled egg
in the fridge.

146
00:12:39,524 --> 00:12:41,475
Well, then take out the yolk.

147
00:12:42,710 --> 00:12:45,880
Look, T.J., I don't have
time for this right now.

148
00:12:46,814 --> 00:12:49,617
No. I'm not looking
for him.

149
00:12:49,685 --> 00:12:51,135
I got to go.

150
00:13:13,742 --> 00:13:15,059
Shit!

151
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:24,902
I'm not leaving it.

152
00:13:24,969 --> 00:13:27,872
I got a friend
who might buy that.

153
00:13:27,939 --> 00:13:29,423
It's not for sale.

154
00:13:29,491 --> 00:13:32,860
He'll pay more than
it's worth. Maybe 2,000.

155
00:13:32,927 --> 00:13:34,178
Why's that?

156
00:13:35,013 --> 00:13:36,697
He's a smuggler.

157
00:13:36,765 --> 00:13:40,301
He's always looking for cars
with button-release trunks.

158
00:13:41,820 --> 00:13:44,472
You don't need
papers or anything.

159
00:13:46,207 --> 00:13:48,258
Where does he live?

160
00:13:48,326 --> 00:13:50,661
Through the woods.
Not far.

161
00:13:50,729 --> 00:13:52,563
What's in it for you?

162
00:13:52,630 --> 00:13:55,732
He'll give me something
for finding it.

163
00:14:00,372 --> 00:14:03,640
If you try anything,
I'm not afraid to use this.

164
00:14:04,509 --> 00:14:05,643
Yeah.

165
00:14:21,860 --> 00:14:23,427
Turn up there.
- Where?

166
00:14:23,494 --> 00:14:25,062
Up at those trees.

167
00:14:26,581 --> 00:14:27,914
There's no road.

168
00:14:27,982 --> 00:14:29,550
There's a path.

169
00:14:30,802 --> 00:14:32,253
It's not far.

170
00:14:41,396 --> 00:14:43,247
I'm not crossing that.

171
00:14:43,314 --> 00:14:45,866
Don't worry.
There's no black ice.

172
00:14:46,635 --> 00:14:48,168
That's Canada.

173
00:14:48,236 --> 00:14:50,137
That's Mohawk land.

174
00:14:50,204 --> 00:14:52,840
The rez is on both
sides of the river.

175
00:14:52,908 --> 00:14:54,141
What about
the border patrol?

176
00:14:54,208 --> 00:14:55,743
There's no border.

177
00:14:57,345 --> 00:14:59,246
I'm still
not crossing that.

178
00:14:59,313 --> 00:15:00,848
Don't worry.
It'll hold a Spirit.

179
00:15:00,916 --> 00:15:02,716
I've seen semis cross it.

180
00:15:04,836 --> 00:15:06,703
The only other way is
the Cornwall Bridge,

181
00:15:06,772 --> 00:15:09,106
and they're not going
to let you take that.

182
00:15:12,945 --> 00:15:15,146
They plow it
and everything.

183
00:15:18,850 --> 00:15:21,385
This is
so fucking stupid.

184
00:16:06,380 --> 00:16:09,750
Better pick up some speed
to get up the bank.

185
00:16:09,818 --> 00:16:12,703
It's just on the other
side of those trees.

186
00:16:38,362 --> 00:16:39,863
(DOG BARKING)

187
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:43,601
LILA: Honk the horn.

188
00:16:43,668 --> 00:16:44,968
(HORN HONKING)

189
00:16:47,555 --> 00:16:48,806
No.

190
00:16:48,873 --> 00:16:51,691
Keep your mouth shut.
Just keep it shut. Okay?

191
00:16:53,060 --> 00:16:54,695
Thunder, shut up!

192
00:16:54,763 --> 00:16:56,713
Get back under there!

193
00:17:02,220 --> 00:17:03,671
He don't like
whites, Lila.

194
00:17:03,738 --> 00:17:05,305
LILA: Sorry.
And you're late.

195
00:17:05,373 --> 00:17:06,690
I'm sorry.

196
00:17:06,758 --> 00:17:09,009
I shouldn't even
be dealing with you.

197
00:17:09,744 --> 00:17:11,612
Count it.

198
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:12,763
What's going on here?

199
00:17:12,830 --> 00:17:14,098
Just count it.

200
00:17:20,087 --> 00:17:21,789
Come on. How much?

201
00:17:23,407 --> 00:17:24,941
How much is there?

202
00:17:27,078 --> 00:17:28,245
1,200.

203
00:17:35,003 --> 00:17:36,853
Who the fuck are they?

204
00:17:38,406 --> 00:17:40,824
Never mind.

205
00:17:40,891 --> 00:17:43,360
I'm not going anywhere until
those people get out of my trunk.

206
00:17:43,428 --> 00:17:45,879
I'll give you half.
Now, let's go.

207
00:17:45,946 --> 00:17:46,980
Let's go!

208
00:17:47,048 --> 00:17:48,549
I'm not taking them
across the border.

209
00:17:48,616 --> 00:17:50,300
It's a crime.
- There's no border here.

210
00:17:50,368 --> 00:17:52,219
This is free trade
between nations.

211
00:17:52,286 --> 00:17:53,320
This isn't a nation.

212
00:17:53,387 --> 00:17:54,521
Let's go.

213
00:18:15,193 --> 00:18:17,894
Why'd your husband
leave you?

214
00:18:17,963 --> 00:18:19,330
Fuck you.

215
00:18:19,397 --> 00:18:22,099
Maybe he wanted
a younger woman.

216
00:18:22,167 --> 00:18:25,318
That's what usually happens.

217
00:18:25,386 --> 00:18:28,555
I never have to worry about that.
My husband's dead.

218
00:18:28,623 --> 00:18:31,608
He went down
in the river on a run.

219
00:18:31,676 --> 00:18:33,761
They never found him.

220
00:18:33,828 --> 00:18:37,080
Probably tangled in the
river weeds somewhere.

221
00:18:37,148 --> 00:18:38,632
You better slow down.
There's ruts out here.

222
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,667
You could get us
stuck in one.

223
00:18:48,092 --> 00:18:49,593
Keep going.

224
00:18:50,495 --> 00:18:51,829
Keep going.

225
00:18:51,896 --> 00:18:53,413
What if the troopers
stop us?

226
00:18:53,448 --> 00:18:56,599
They're not going to stop you.
You're white.

227
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:32,736
LILA: Stop and wait for him
to come to the window.

228
00:19:40,295 --> 00:19:42,212
Roll down your window.

229
00:19:44,665 --> 00:19:46,049
Count it.

230
00:19:55,893 --> 00:19:57,094
1,200.

231
00:20:04,686 --> 00:20:06,069
Let's go.

232
00:20:16,281 --> 00:20:17,997
Stop at those trees.

233
00:20:24,973 --> 00:20:26,707
Now open the door.

234
00:20:27,742 --> 00:20:28,959
Open it!

235
00:20:30,779 --> 00:20:31,912
Now get out.

236
00:20:31,980 --> 00:20:33,280
You can't have my car.
- Get out!

237
00:20:33,347 --> 00:20:35,716
You can't have
my car. No!

238
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:40,771
(BOTH GRUNTING)

239
00:20:40,838 --> 00:20:42,089
(RAY SHOUTS)

240
00:20:55,820 --> 00:20:57,254
(SIGHING)

241
00:21:22,747 --> 00:21:25,248
I told you not to use that
thing when I'm not here.

242
00:21:25,316 --> 00:21:27,901
If I get it working,
I can sell it.

243
00:21:27,969 --> 00:21:31,321
I don't care. Don't use
that thing when I'm not here!

244
00:21:34,442 --> 00:21:35,559
Rent-to-Own called.

245
00:21:35,626 --> 00:21:36,676
They said they're
coming to get the TV

246
00:21:36,744 --> 00:21:38,795
if you don't pay
by 4:00 tomorrow.

247
00:21:41,081 --> 00:21:42,733
Did you find him?

248
00:21:43,667 --> 00:21:45,002
No.

249
00:21:46,237 --> 00:21:48,288
Where was the car?

250
00:21:48,355 --> 00:21:50,773
At the bus stop
on the rez.

251
00:21:50,841 --> 00:21:52,142
I bet he went
to Atlantic City.

252
00:21:52,209 --> 00:21:53,310
You don't know that.

253
00:21:53,378 --> 00:21:54,944
Yeah, well,
you can find out.

254
00:21:55,013 --> 00:21:57,114
Go to the bus station, see what
buses came through last night.

255
00:21:57,181 --> 00:21:58,681
And what?
Chase him across the country?

256
00:21:58,749 --> 00:22:00,400
