you got a job.

532
00:42:43,126 --> 00:42:44,309
Huh?

533
00:42:44,377 --> 00:42:47,146
Get your jacket.
Let's go. I got coffee.

534
00:42:54,838 --> 00:42:56,122
Where are we going?

535
00:42:56,189 --> 00:42:58,590
Get in. I'll tell you
on the way.

536
00:43:05,766 --> 00:43:07,700
Rita said you quit.

537
00:43:07,768 --> 00:43:09,234
She fired me.

538
00:43:09,302 --> 00:43:10,369
That's not
what she told me.

539
00:43:10,437 --> 00:43:11,720
Well, she should have.

540
00:43:11,788 --> 00:43:14,573
I couldn't see to count the money.
I told you that.

541
00:43:14,641 --> 00:43:16,742
It was coming up
short half the time.

542
00:43:16,809 --> 00:43:18,510
Then get some glasses.

543
00:43:18,578 --> 00:43:20,596
They make me carsick.

544
00:43:21,047 --> 00:43:22,998
So where are we going?

545
00:43:23,733 --> 00:43:25,000
The Tribal Council.

546
00:43:25,067 --> 00:43:26,302
They need someone
to answer phones.

547
00:43:26,369 --> 00:43:28,069
No! No way!

548
00:43:28,137 --> 00:43:29,605
Why? You can't
answer phones?

549
00:43:29,673 --> 00:43:31,640
Not there.
Not with them.

550
00:43:34,777 --> 00:43:36,211
What's that?

551
00:43:37,013 --> 00:43:38,347
I bought it.

552
00:43:38,414 --> 00:43:39,849
From who?

553
00:43:39,916 --> 00:43:41,434
Some white lady.

554
00:43:43,820 --> 00:43:44,920
What?

555
00:43:44,988 --> 00:43:46,755
What do you need
a car for?

556
00:43:46,790 --> 00:43:47,772
To get to work.

557
00:43:47,840 --> 00:43:49,708
So I don't have to walk
in the breakdown lane.

558
00:43:49,775 --> 00:43:52,428
Last week,
I almost got hit by a plow.

559
00:43:52,496 --> 00:43:53,545
You'll live.

560
00:43:53,613 --> 00:43:56,248
And you know what
I'm talking about.

561
00:43:59,852 --> 00:44:01,804
All right, all right.
I'll go.

562
00:44:03,156 --> 00:44:04,489
Let's go!

563
00:44:25,729 --> 00:44:27,446
$3.76.

564
00:44:27,514 --> 00:44:28,848
I got exact.

565
00:44:48,401 --> 00:44:50,385
Do I have any messages?

566
00:45:03,683 --> 00:45:05,517
I can't read this.

567
00:45:07,303 --> 00:45:09,004
(SIGHING)

568
00:45:09,072 --> 00:45:11,173
<i>(CHATTERING ON RADIO)</i>

569
00:45:12,175 --> 00:45:14,510
That's a "T."

570
00:45:14,577 --> 00:45:16,761
No, I can't read
any of it.

571
00:45:16,829 --> 00:45:19,281
I told Bernie
I couldn't see.

572
00:45:22,485 --> 00:45:23,685
Never mind.

573
00:45:24,520 --> 00:45:25,821
I'll go.

574
00:45:43,873 --> 00:45:47,209
We got to go to Wolfmart and get some
anti-freeze, unless you got extra.

575
00:45:47,277 --> 00:45:48,293
Why?

576
00:45:48,361 --> 00:45:49,645
I think you got a leak
in your heater coil.

577
00:45:49,712 --> 00:45:51,479
It's making
your windows fog up.

578
00:45:51,514 --> 00:45:55,333
We better hurry, because I
got nothing for under the tree.

579
00:47:19,519 --> 00:47:21,169
(BABY CRYING)

580
00:47:35,352 --> 00:47:36,702
<i>MAN ON RADIO:</i>
<i>Cold snap for tonight</i>

581
00:47:36,769 --> 00:47:39,771
<i>with low temperatures dropping down to</i>
<i>19 below Fahrenheit.</i>

582
00:47:39,839 --> 00:47:43,758
<i>Very hazardous for the cars</i>
<i>and also the Ski-Doos.</i>

583
00:47:43,826 --> 00:47:46,044
<i>Stay off the roads if you can.</i>

584
00:47:46,112 --> 00:47:49,882
<i>Currently outside our C-Tribe Radio
