586
00:47:55,722 --> 00:47:58,289
Mohawks don't
celebrate Christmas.

587
00:47:58,357 --> 00:48:02,327
You could have fooled me, the way they
were all lined up at Yankee Dollar today.

588
00:48:02,395 --> 00:48:04,863
Those are Christians,
the converted.

589
00:48:04,931 --> 00:48:06,899
From what?

590
00:48:06,966 --> 00:48:08,800
The Longhouse ways.

591
00:48:09,936 --> 00:48:13,338
That's messed up,
not having Santa Claus.

592
00:48:13,406 --> 00:48:15,340
For the kids, I mean.

593
00:48:17,377 --> 00:48:18,493
RICKY: The oxygen.

594
00:48:18,561 --> 00:48:19,678
(GASPING)

595
00:48:19,745 --> 00:48:21,279
(MIMICKING PUNCHING SOUNDS)

596
00:48:21,965 --> 00:48:23,682
(SHOUTS)

597
00:48:23,750 --> 00:48:25,234
<i>MALE ANNOUNCER: It's the Blast and Crash Track set.</i>
<i>BOY: Go!</i>

598
00:48:25,385 --> 00:48:27,068
<i>You've timed it right</i>
<i>to slam your competition.</i>

599
00:48:27,103 --> 00:48:28,737
<i>So load, lock and launch...</i>

600
00:48:28,804 --> 00:48:31,140
Dad's going to get
me that for Christmas.

601
00:48:31,207 --> 00:48:33,425
Yeah? What about
Santa Claus?

602
00:48:33,493 --> 00:48:36,995
Santa Claus is going
to get me the house for Christmas.

603
00:48:37,063 --> 00:48:38,113
<i>ANNOUNCER: You got him!</i>
<i>BOY: Yeah!</i>

604
00:48:46,422 --> 00:48:48,473
Wait.
They're not Chinese.

605
00:48:49,475 --> 00:48:51,576
LILA: They're Pakis.

606
00:48:51,644 --> 00:48:52,911
What's that mean?

607
00:48:52,978 --> 00:48:54,395
They're from Pakistan.

608
00:48:54,463 --> 00:48:55,731
Well, where's that?

609
00:48:55,798 --> 00:48:56,832
I don't know.
What difference does it make?

610
00:48:56,899 --> 00:48:58,684
A big difference.

611
00:49:01,271 --> 00:49:04,540
If we wait much longer, we're not going
to be able to get back across the river.

612
00:49:04,607 --> 00:49:07,359
Look, I'm not driving just
anybody across the border.

613
00:49:07,426 --> 00:49:08,794
Do you want the money?

614
00:49:08,862 --> 00:49:11,613
I want to know
what's in that bag.

615
00:49:11,681 --> 00:49:13,282
What's in there?

616
00:49:16,735 --> 00:49:18,336
They don't understand you.

617
00:49:18,404 --> 00:49:19,871
Well, if they want
to come here so bad,

618
00:49:19,939 --> 00:49:21,706
they should take the time
to learn English.

619
00:49:21,774 --> 00:49:23,525
Hold on a second.

620
00:49:24,961 --> 00:49:26,712
RAY: (EXCLAIMING)
Hold on a second.

621
00:49:36,756 --> 00:49:37,756
LILA: What are you doing?

622
00:49:37,824 --> 00:49:39,424
Just count the money
and let's go.

623
00:49:39,492 --> 00:49:42,961
If we get stuck on the river,
it won't matter what's in there.

624
00:49:43,028 --> 00:49:44,362
RAY: Let's just hope
they're not the ones

625
00:49:44,430 --> 00:49:46,731
that blow themselves
and everyone else up.

626
00:49:53,456 --> 00:49:55,373
We don't have time.

627
00:50:04,083 --> 00:50:06,318
Is that a 20 or a 50?

628
00:50:06,753 --> 00:50:07,786
50.

629
00:50:16,362 --> 00:50:17,762
Shit.

630
00:50:22,201 --> 00:50:23,835
What are you doing?

631
00:50:23,903 --> 00:50:27,105
Nuclear power,
poison gas.

632
00:50:27,173 --> 00:50:29,657
RAY: Who knows what they
might have in there?

633
00:50:32,462 --> 00:50:35,330
I'm not going to be
responsible for that.

634
00:50:40,920 --> 00:50:43,488
Hey, I'm going to be
a little late. Okay?

635
00:50:44,440 --> 00:50:46,275
I'm at work.

636
00:50:46,342 --> 00:50:47,976
Is Ricky asleep?

637
00:50:48,744 --> 00:50:51,013
Put him on.

638
00:50:51,080 --> 00:50:54,950
Now listen, Ricky, he's not
coming till you go to sleep.

639
00:50:56,819 --> 00:50:58,486
No. Not yet.

640
00:50:59,622 --> 00:51:02,958
He's still flying
over Canada.

641
00:51:03,026 --> 00:51:04,927
He's not even done
with Canada yet,

642
00:51:04,994 --> 00:51:08,096
so he's not coming
until you get to sleep.

643
00:51:08,998 --> 00:51:10,882
<i>(MUSIC PLAYING ON TV)</i>

644
00:51:13,485 --> 00:51:15,470
Hi. Is Mitch there?

