652
00:51:40,679 --> 00:51:44,082
On Moira Road, off of 37.

653
00:51:45,368 --> 00:51:46,885
Mmm-hmm.

654
00:51:47,586 --> 00:51:49,554
One more thing.

655
00:51:49,622 --> 00:51:54,292
(WHISPERING) Can you go to Kmart and
pick me up a Blast and Crash Track set?

656
00:51:57,263 --> 00:51:58,279
Yeah, exactly.

657
00:51:58,398 --> 00:51:59,397
(LAUGHS)

658
00:51:59,432 --> 00:52:01,216
Uh, thanks, man.

659
00:52:02,218 --> 00:52:04,519
T.J., look at me.

660
00:52:04,586 --> 00:52:06,771
Yeah, that's pretty cool, but it's
going to hurt when you sit down.

661
00:52:06,839 --> 00:52:09,824
Now, unwrap yourself.
It's dinnertime.

662
00:52:17,216 --> 00:52:18,450
(PIPES CREAKING)

663
00:52:24,240 --> 00:52:26,941
Hey, I'll be
right back. Okay?

664
00:53:16,993 --> 00:53:18,609
DEALER:
They say there's a bag.

665
00:53:18,678 --> 00:53:20,562
It was too heavy.
We had to unload it.

666
00:53:20,630 --> 00:53:22,547
(WOMAN SPEAKING IN URDU)

667
00:53:25,301 --> 00:53:28,270
What's the matter with her?
What's she saying?

668
00:53:28,338 --> 00:53:31,455
DEALER: That bag,
her baby is in the bag.

669
00:53:31,523 --> 00:53:33,458
(WOMAN SPEAKING IN URDU)

670
00:53:36,696 --> 00:53:38,897
RAY: It didn't feel like
there was anything in that bag.

671
00:53:38,965 --> 00:53:40,399
LILA: We got to go back.

672
00:53:40,466 --> 00:53:42,417
I know. I know that.

673
00:53:50,292 --> 00:53:51,292
T.J.: Hey.

674
00:53:52,912 --> 00:53:54,179
MITCH: This the right one?

675
00:53:54,213 --> 00:53:55,814
Uh, yeah.

676
00:53:56,716 --> 00:53:57,949
(CHUCKLING) Yeah.

677
00:54:02,154 --> 00:54:04,422
Thanks, man.
Have a merry one.

678
00:54:04,489 --> 00:54:05,707
Okay.

679
00:54:06,843 --> 00:54:08,376
(T.J. HUMMING)

680
00:54:52,421 --> 00:54:55,623
Look. There. Tracks.

681
00:54:55,691 --> 00:54:57,726
Where?
- Up there.

682
00:54:59,228 --> 00:55:01,963
Slow down.
I don't want to run over it.

683
00:55:06,235 --> 00:55:08,102
Stop.
I think it was here.

684
00:55:33,846 --> 00:55:35,013
(LILA GASPING)

685
00:55:36,148 --> 00:55:37,682
It's dead.

686
00:55:41,486 --> 00:55:42,887
Oh, my God.

687
00:55:53,665 --> 00:55:54,999
Come on.

688
00:56:14,220 --> 00:56:15,720
(SCOFFS)

689
00:56:15,787 --> 00:56:17,155
It's dead.

690
00:56:19,124 --> 00:56:20,892
Tap the bottom
of his feet.

691
00:56:20,960 --> 00:56:23,211
Why?

692
00:56:23,362 --> 00:56:25,796
That's what they did to get
Ricky breathing when he was born.

693
00:56:25,865 --> 00:56:27,265
I don't want to touch it.

694
00:56:27,333 --> 00:56:29,367
I can't hold it
and drive.

695
00:56:30,569 --> 00:56:32,103
(HEATER BLOWING)

696
00:56:33,856 --> 00:56:35,874
I don't think it matters.

697
00:56:37,509 --> 00:56:39,510
Just hold it next to your body.
Keep him warm.

698
00:56:39,578 --> 00:56:41,645
But it's too late!

699
00:56:41,713 --> 00:56:44,916
Just do it. We can't
give it back to her cold.

700
00:57:14,046 --> 00:57:15,646
(SIREN SOUNDING)

701
00:57:16,966 --> 00:57:19,918
Shit! Shit!

702
00:57:19,985 --> 00:57:23,471
What do I do?
- Calm down! Pull over.

703
00:57:23,506 --> 00:57:25,807
What if he saw us go by
before to the Pioneer?

704
00:57:25,875 --> 00:57:29,210
He's got no reason to stop us, unless you
give him one. Just keep your mouth shut.

705
00:57:29,278 --> 00:57:31,212
What if he searches the car?
What do we say about...

706
00:57:31,280 --> 00:57:34,049
He won't!
Just remember, you're white!

707
00:57:57,189 --> 00:57:59,157
License and registration.

708
00:58:11,620 --> 00:58:13,855
Could you step out of the
vehicle, please, ma'am?

709
00:58:13,890 --> 00:58:15,924
I wasn't speeding, was I?

710
00:58:17,226 --> 00:58:18,526
Did I do something?

711
00:58:18,594 --> 00:58:21,463
I'm just directing you
to step out of the vehicle.

712
00:58:21,530 --> 00:58:22,496
Okay.

713
00:58:28,454 --> 00:58:30,388
Step behind the vehicle.

714
00:58:39,031 --> 00:58:40,165
You see that?

715
00:58:41,233 --> 00:58:42,817
Oh!

716
00:58:42,885 --> 00:58:47,021
Your left rear parking light,
it's not illuminated.

717
00:58:47,139 --> 00:58:50,058
Oh, I didn't know.

718
00:58:50,175 --> 00:58:52,777
I'm going to have to give
you a provisional ticket.

719
00:58:52,845 --> 00:58:56,297
As long as you get it repaired within
48 hours, it won't be a problem.

720
00:58:56,365 --> 00:58:58,082
Thanks.

721
00:58:58,150 --> 00:59:00,251
Who's your friend?

722
00:59:00,318 --> 00:59:04,472
She takes care of my kids
when I have to work late.

723
00:59:04,540 --> 00:59:06,641
You can step back
in the vehicle.

724
00:59:17,253 --> 00:59:19,287
<i>(CHILDREN CHEERING ON TV)</i>

725
00:59:35,354 --> 00:59:37,037
We got to take it in.

726
00:59:40,025 --> 00:59:41,659
What is it?

727
00:59:43,229 --> 00:59:44,995
It's moving.

728
00:59:45,063 --> 00:59:46,881
What? Are you sure?

729
00:59:50,469 --> 00:59:52,169
(RAY EXCLAIMING)

730
00:59:52,671 --> 00:59:54,822
Hello, little baby.

731
00:59:54,890 --> 00:59:56,557
He was just cold.

732
00:59:58,761 --> 00:59:59,894
(BABY WHIMPERING)

733
01:00:48,360 --> 01:00:49,844
We found him.

734
01:01:04,409 --> 01:01:05,709
(BABY WHIMPERING)

735
01:01:17,339 --> 01:01:18,690
(WOMAN CRYING)

736
01:01:26,048 --> 01:01:27,514
Come on. Let's go.

737
01:01:38,844 --> 01:01:40,244
He was dead.

738
01:01:42,781 --> 01:01:44,382
He was just cold.

739
01:01:45,985 --> 01:01:47,218
He was dead.

740
01:01:48,854 --> 01:01:50,454
Okay. Whatever.

741
01:01:52,090 --> 01:01:55,593
He was dead.
You brought him back to life.

742
01:01:55,661 --> 01:01:58,129
That was the Creator,
not me.

743
01:02:05,771 --> 01:02:07,405
All I know is
Kmart is closed,

744
01:02:07,472 --> 01:02:09,541
and I got nothing
for under the tree.

745
01:03:03,395 --> 01:03:04,629
Here.

746
01:03:07,800 --> 01:03:10,534
Merry Christmas
or whatever.

747
01:03:11,570 --> 01:03:12,670
Yeah.

748
01:03:50,608 --> 01:03:52,043
Bernie!

749
01:04:19,388 --> 01:04:20,738
<i>(CHATTERING ON TV)</i>

750
01:04:26,745 --> 01:04:28,296
What's that?

751
01:04:29,331 --> 01:04:31,165
Hot Wheels.

752
01:04:31,233 --> 01:04:32,633
Where'd you get it?

753
01:04:32,700 --> 01:04:34,501
I called a friend.

754
01:04:35,237 --> 01:04:36,938
That kid Mitch?

755
01:04:37,005 --> 01:04:39,740
It's probably stolen.
- It's not stolen.

756
01:04:39,808 --> 01:04:42,643
I don't want you hanging around
with him. That kid is bad news.

757
01:04:42,710 --> 01:04:44,345
It's not like you
were going to get it.

758
01:04:44,413 --> 01:04:45,712
Move it.

759
01:04:45,780 --> 01:04:48,700
Move it! Listen, mister.

760
01:04:48,767 --> 01:04:51,952
I got more important things
to worry about than toys.

761
01:04:52,020 --> 01:04:53,554
I'm trying to get
our doublewide.

762
01:04:53,622 --> 01:04:55,590
(SARCASTICALLY) Oh, yeah.
I forgot about that.

763
01:04:55,658 --> 01:04:57,925
You can lose
that attitude.

764
01:04:59,762 --> 01:05:03,130
Anyway, Kmart was closed
by the time I got off work.

765
01:05:04,933 --> 01:05:06,467
What's that smell?

766
01:05:08,604 --> 01:05:09,821
Popcorn.

767
01:05:15,344 --> 01:05:18,680
Hi, it's me.
I can't get to the phone right now.

768
01:05:18,747 --> 01:05:21,683
Please leave a message.
And, Troy, if it's you, please,

769
01:05:21,750 --> 01:05:23,651
at least let us
know you're alive.

770
01:05:23,719 --> 01:05:25,920
The boys are really
worried about you.

771
01:05:28,357 --> 01:05:29,690
(SIGHING)

772
01:05:36,198 --> 01:05:37,564
(RICKY CHATTERING)

773
01:05:39,067 --> 01:05:41,068
<i>(CHATTERING ON TV)</i>

774
01:05:50,979 --> 01:05:51,962
Daddy!

775
01:05:58,236 --> 01:06:00,103
Is there a Ray Eddy here?

776
01:06:00,171 --> 01:06:01,773
Yes.

777
01:06:02,974 --> 01:06:04,275
Can I talk to you
outside for a minute?

778
01:06:04,342 --> 01:06:06,510
I haven't gotten
that light fixed yet.

779
01:06:06,545 --> 01:06:08,011
It's not about that.

780
01:06:08,080 --> 01:06:10,097
I just have
a few questions.

781
01:06:10,165 --> 01:06:12,717
Uh, sure. One second.

782
01:06:16,939 --> 01:06:19,056
I'll be back in a second.

783
01:06:22,661 --> 01:06:24,978
This is about the woman
that was with you.

784
01:06:25,013 --> 01:06:26,430
Yeah.

785
01:06:26,465 --> 01:06:28,232
How long have you
known her?

786
01:06:28,300 --> 01:06:31,385
Not long.
She looks after my kids.

787
01:06:33,254 --> 01:06:35,255
She's a smuggler.

788
01:06:35,323 --> 01:06:36,974
Really?

789
01:06:37,041 --> 01:06:39,560
There is that element on the
reservation. I'm sure you know.

790
01:06:39,628 --> 01:06:40,544
Well, I've heard about it.

791
01:06:40,612 --> 01:06:43,447
I had no idea
she was involved.

792
01:06:43,515 --> 01:06:44,982
How did you meet her?

793
01:06:45,050 --> 01:06:46,801
Um...

794
01:06:46,869 --> 01:06:51,038
I think there was a sign
for a babysitter at Wolfmart.

795
01:06:51,973 --> 01:06:53,574
That's where I get my gas.

796
01:06:53,641 --> 01:06:55,876
I just thought you
should be aware of that.

797
01:06:55,944 --> 01:06:58,579
She's known to have brought
illegal aliens into the country.

798
01:06:58,646 --> 01:07:00,798
Oh, my God.

799
01:07:00,865 --> 01:07:02,482
If I were you,
I'd get a new babysitter.

800
01:07:02,550 --> 01:07:04,468
Absolutely.

801
01:07:04,536 --> 01:07:06,971
Well, you have
an enjoyable holiday.

802
01:07:07,155 --> 01:07:08,539
You, too.

803
01:07:28,460 --> 01:07:31,645
T.J., could you
come out here a minute?

804
01:07:31,713 --> 01:07:33,981
T.J., get your ass
out here!

805
01:07:42,457 --> 01:07:44,125
What did he want?
Did something happen to Dad?

806
01:07:44,192 --> 01:07:45,460
No.

807
01:07:45,911 --> 01:07:47,644
What did he want?

808
01:07:47,712 --> 01:07:49,881
Did you have a fire
here last night?

809
01:07:51,750 --> 01:07:54,285
Uh, the pipes froze,
so I fixed them.

810
01:07:54,353 --> 01:07:55,920
You fixed them?

811
01:07:56,922 --> 01:07:57,955
Yeah.

812
01:07:58,023 --> 01:08:00,091
Did you use
the blowtorch?

813
01:08:00,859 --> 01:08:01,859
Dad did it before...

814
01:08:01,927 --> 01:08:03,727
So you used
the blowtorch!

815
01:08:03,795 --> 01:08:05,229
(EXCLAIMING)

816
01:08:05,297 --> 01:08:07,932
Look at this!
We can't live here anymore!

817
01:08:08,000 --> 01:08:09,967
So what?
It's just a tin crapper.

818
01:08:10,035 --> 01:08:13,437
No, this was our house.

819
01:08:13,505 --> 01:08:16,407
So, we're getting
a new one, right?

820
01:08:16,474 --> 01:08:17,942
That's it!

821
01:08:19,311 --> 01:08:20,577
Damn it!
- No. What are you...

822
01:08:20,645 --> 01:08:23,864
Son of a bitch!
Don't touch it!

823
01:08:25,183 --> 01:08:27,217
It's not yours.
Dad gave it to me!

824
01:08:27,285 --> 01:08:28,335
Put it down!

825
01:08:28,403 --> 01:08:29,904
Are you going
to shoot me now, too?

826
01:08:29,972 --> 01:08:31,221
Put it down!
- Maybe he didn't like getting shot

827
01:08:31,289 --> 01:08:34,308
in his own house!
Maybe that's why he left!

828
01:08:34,376 --> 01:08:35,743
That was an accident.
- Yeah, some accident!

829
01:08:35,810 --> 01:08:39,079
You shot him in the foot!

830
01:08:39,147 --> 01:08:42,400
T.J., he spent the food money
on scratch cards.

831
01:08:42,435 --> 01:08:44,268
He'd done it before.

832
01:08:44,336 --> 01:08:47,288
Yeah, and he was clean
32 months since then.

833
01:08:50,125 --> 01:08:53,310
Give me that.
- No, you can't have it. It's mine.

834
01:08:54,012 --> 01:08:55,663
Give it to me!

835
01:09:08,159 --> 01:09:11,528
I didn't know any other way
to keep us together.

836
01:09:11,596 --> 01:09:12,830
I mean,

837
01:09:14,032 --> 01:09:17,668
he's a good dad
when he's not gambling.

838
01:09:19,704 --> 01:09:20,905
Yeah.

839
01:09:21,640 --> 01:09:24,341
Awesome dad.

840
01:09:24,409 --> 01:09:27,395
Robs us and takes off
a week before Christmas.

841
01:10:00,128 --> 01:10:01,478
(SIGHING)

842
01:10:22,134 --> 01:10:23,167
(SIGHS)

843
01:10:23,234 --> 01:10:24,535
I quit smuggling.

844
01:10:24,602 --> 01:10:26,336
T.J. set the trailer
on fire.

845
01:10:26,404 --> 01:10:28,438
He didn't mean to,
but the pipes froze

846
01:10:28,506 --> 01:10:29,807
and he took out
that damn torch,

847
01:10:29,875 --> 01:10:32,643
which I told him not to touch
when I wasn't there,

848
01:10:32,711 --> 01:10:35,146
and he thawed them out.

849
01:10:35,213 --> 01:10:38,049
I got glasses, and I
can see up close now.

850
01:10:38,116 --> 01:10:41,618
There's a hole in my house.
We got to move.

851
01:10:41,687 --> 01:10:45,156
I just need one more run
to get the double.

852
01:10:45,223 --> 01:10:47,825
Look, you can have
the Spirit. Okay?

853
01:10:47,893 --> 01:10:49,760
I don't want it.

854
01:10:49,828 --> 01:10:51,829
What is it then?

855
01:10:51,897 --> 01:10:55,700
You still mad about that baby?
'Cause it wasn't my fault.

856
01:10:55,767 --> 01:10:59,136
I mean, who puts their baby
in a duffle bag?

857
01:10:59,204 --> 01:11:00,838
You're going to need
a lot of money

858
01:11:00,906 --> 01:11:03,074
to raise that
one-year-old kid.

859
01:11:03,709 --> 01:11:05,275
I got enough.

860
01:11:05,343 --> 01:11:08,746
Yeah, but you still
got to get him.

861
01:11:08,813 --> 01:11:12,466
I'll help you.
You can even borrow my gun.

862
01:11:42,980 --> 01:11:45,099
You should see
the inside.

863
01:11:46,201 --> 01:11:48,002
How many bedrooms?
- Three.

864
01:11:48,069 --> 01:11:51,271
And there's a Jacuzzi tub
in the master bathroom.

865
01:11:52,607 --> 01:11:53,607
Wall-to-wall carpet?

866
01:11:53,674 --> 01:11:54,708
Oh, yeah.

867
01:11:54,775 --> 01:11:56,843
But the best thing
is the insulation.

868
01:11:56,911 --> 01:11:59,013
Pipes can never freeze.

869
01:11:59,080 --> 01:12:00,814
I'll be right back.

870
01:12:07,472 --> 01:12:11,041
VERSAILLES: There's never any need
to touch up or repaint these walls.

871
01:12:12,210 --> 01:12:14,362
I want to schedule
a delivery.

872
01:12:16,581 --> 01:12:19,282
Just give me one sec.

873
01:12:19,350 --> 01:12:21,585
What exactly is it
I can do for you?

874
01:12:23,237 --> 01:12:26,157
It's 3,000, but I want
it delivered tomorrow.

875
01:12:26,224 --> 01:12:29,026
You did have a closing date
on Christmas.

876
01:12:30,762 --> 01:12:32,246
I'm here now.

877
01:12:32,313 --> 01:12:33,464
You add this
to my deposit.

878
01:12:33,531 --> 01:12:34,765
All you have to do
is show up.

879
01:12:34,833 --> 01:12:38,969
If I don't have the rest,
you can keep it.

880
01:12:39,036 --> 01:12:42,573
All right, well,
I just need you to sign this paper here,

881
01:12:42,640 --> 01:12:45,242
and you'll be ready to go.
Right there.

882
01:12:52,550 --> 01:12:54,267
I'm sorry about that.

883
01:13:00,458 --> 01:13:01,976
(HORN HONKING)

884
01:13:16,024 --> 01:13:17,157
Heat wave.

885
01:13:17,225 --> 01:13:19,059
You got a run
for us, Jimmy?

886
01:13:19,127 --> 01:13:20,994
It's pretty slow
after Christmas,

887
01:13:21,062 --> 01:13:23,196
unless you want
to go off the rez.

888
01:13:25,066 --> 01:13:26,366
There's that guy
up in Montreal.

889
01:13:26,435 --> 01:13:28,068
He's usually got heads.

890
01:13:38,863 --> 01:13:40,514
<i>(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

891
01:13:59,951 --> 01:14:01,851
What? You want a job?

892
01:14:02,904 --> 01:14:04,288
No, Jimmy sent us.

893
01:14:08,259 --> 01:14:09,576
BRUNO: Christy.

894
01:14:11,946 --> 01:14:13,647
Put your hands up.

895
01:14:23,558 --> 01:14:25,475
CHRISTY: They have nothing.

896
01:14:25,926 --> 01:14:27,244
BRUNO: Okay.

897
01:14:54,672 --> 01:14:56,406
Pop the back.

898
01:14:58,643 --> 01:15:00,811
We need to get paid first.

899
01:15:00,879 --> 01:15:02,295
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

900
01:15:15,910 --> 01:15:17,444
There's only 600 here.

901
01:15:17,511 --> 01:15:18,295
(AGREES IN FRENCH)

902
01:15:18,362 --> 01:15:20,697
You get the rest
at the drop off.

903
01:15:20,765 --> 01:15:22,699
It's 600 apiece.

904
01:15:22,750 --> 01:15:24,801
You want to make
a change now?

905
01:15:29,924 --> 01:15:31,591
It's 1,200.

906
01:15:31,659 --> 01:15:34,227
You want to have
a problem?

907
01:15:34,295 --> 01:15:36,613
BRUNO: Huh?

908
01:15:36,681 --> 01:15:40,584
Because it's not a problem for me.
It is a problem for them!

909
01:15:40,651 --> 01:15:41,751
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

910
01:15:41,819 --> 01:15:43,387
Hey!

911
01:15:43,455 --> 01:15:44,488
(BRUNO GRUNTING)

912
01:15:44,556 --> 01:15:45,823
Okay. Okay.
We'll take them.

913
01:15:45,890 --> 01:15:47,524
We'll take them with us.
Open the trunk.

914
01:15:47,592 --> 01:15:48,475
LILA: Let's go!

915
01:15:48,542 --> 01:15:49,726
Just open the trunk.

916
01:15:59,487 --> 01:16:00,520
BRUNO: In.

917
01:16:01,856 --> 01:16:03,257
Bitch.

918
01:16:03,324 --> 01:16:05,459
(MUMBLING)

919
01:16:05,526 --> 01:16:07,093
Turn around!
(GASPS) - Bruno!

920
01:16:09,697 --> 01:16:11,332
I want the rest.

921
01:16:14,052 --> 01:16:15,836
But I have nothing.

922
01:16:18,022 --> 01:16:19,056
(GUN FIRES)

923
01:16:23,061 --> 01:16:24,995
(CHRISTY SPEAKING IN FRENCH)

924
01:16:29,283 --> 01:16:31,218
(SIGHING)

925
01:16:31,285 --> 01:16:33,736
LILA: Let's go!
Let's get out of here.

926
01:16:33,804 --> 01:16:35,089
I'll give you
the rest of the money.

927
01:16:35,156 --> 01:16:36,624
No. Thanks.

928
01:16:36,691 --> 01:16:39,109
You're going to
get us all killed.

929
01:16:42,547 --> 01:16:44,848
RAY: Give it to her.
Give it to her.

930
01:16:52,056 --> 01:16:55,342
(SPEAKING IN FRENCH)

931
01:17:00,215 --> 01:17:01,147
(RAY SHOUTS)

932
01:17:05,169 --> 01:17:08,271
He shot me. I'm shot.

933
01:17:08,339 --> 01:17:10,941
I think you're okay.

934
01:17:11,008 --> 01:17:12,742
You should have just
took the money from me.

935
01:17:12,810 --> 01:17:15,345
I'm sick and tired of people
stealing from me. Is it all there?

936
01:17:15,413 --> 01:17:16,963
We got to get
out of here first.

937
01:17:16,998 --> 01:17:18,848
Just count it.
Make sure it's all there.

938
01:17:18,916 --> 01:17:20,501
Okay, okay. All right.

939
01:17:23,738 --> 01:17:25,539
Is it there?

940
01:17:25,607 --> 01:17:26,907
It's all there.

941
01:17:26,975 --> 01:17:28,675
Good.

942
01:17:28,743 --> 01:17:31,411
Slow down a bit. We got to
keep it under the speed limit.

943
01:17:31,546 --> 01:17:33,696
We got to get off
this road.

944
01:17:36,500 --> 01:17:39,102
We got to get
off this road.

945
01:17:39,170 --> 01:17:40,703
(SIREN WAILING)

946
01:17:42,256 --> 01:17:43,490
Oh, shit!

947
01:17:48,997 --> 01:17:50,447
Where's the reservation?

948
01:17:50,515 --> 01:17:52,933
Just past that pole
right there.

949
01:18:04,378 --> 01:18:06,897
What the hell?
We're on the rez.

950
01:18:06,964 --> 01:18:09,249
They can't arrest us, but if they
catch us they can take the money.

951
01:18:09,317 --> 01:18:10,316
Shit!

952
01:18:27,218 --> 01:18:29,168
It's black ice
out here.

953
01:18:29,236 --> 01:18:30,937
Will it hold us?

954
01:18:31,005 --> 01:18:32,305
I don't know.

955
01:18:44,152 --> 01:18:45,185
RAY: Shit.

956
01:18:59,984 --> 01:19:02,352
(CHATTERING IN FRENCH)

957
01:19:18,169 --> 01:19:20,887
LILA: Get out on your side!
Pop the trunk!

958
01:19:20,955 --> 01:19:21,971
Get the cash.
You got the cash?

959
01:19:22,123 --> 01:19:23,189
LILA: Yeah.

960
01:19:24,291 --> 01:19:25,425
Come on. Let's go.

961
01:19:25,493 --> 01:19:27,160
Come on, come on.

962
01:19:27,228 --> 01:19:28,929
(WOMEN WHIMPERING)

963
01:19:29,948 --> 01:19:31,481
(WOMEN SPEAKING MANDARIN)

964
01:19:43,694 --> 01:19:45,062
(SIREN WAILING)

965
01:19:45,213 --> 01:19:47,097
<i>(CHATTERING ON POLICE RADIO)</i>

966
01:19:57,625 --> 01:19:59,993
JIMMY: Hey, Lila!
Over here!

967
01:20:06,350 --> 01:20:07,751
(HORN HONKS)

968
01:20:20,014 --> 01:20:22,482
Jimmy, you're not
coming in here.

969
01:20:22,550 --> 01:20:25,034
JIMMY: We just need to
borrow your oven.

970
01:20:33,928 --> 01:20:37,130
THREE RIVERS: We have a situation
with a couple of smugglers.

971
01:20:37,198 --> 01:20:40,100
They tried to go across the river,
but their car went in.

972
01:20:40,167 --> 01:20:43,520
And now the troopers know that
they're on the reservation.

973
01:20:43,588 --> 01:20:45,054
ROSALIE: Who are they?

974
01:20:45,122 --> 01:20:47,256
Lila Littlewolf
and some white woman.

975
01:20:47,324 --> 01:20:48,892
ROSALIE: What do
the troopers want?

976
01:20:48,960 --> 01:20:51,161
They want the surrender
of the two illegals.

977
01:20:51,228 --> 01:20:54,614
Second, they want the surrender
of the non-native smuggler.

978
01:20:54,681 --> 01:20:57,266
They really mean to set
an example over here.

979
01:20:57,334 --> 01:20:58,584
Do you know
where they are?

980
01:20:58,652 --> 01:21:00,820
Yeah. They're probably
over at Velma's.

981
01:21:00,888 --> 01:21:02,572
ROSALIE: What about
Lila Littlewolf?

982
01:21:02,640 --> 01:21:05,592
You can't start throwing
Mohawks off the rez, Rosalie.

983
01:21:05,659 --> 01:21:07,844
She's got a Mohawk son.

984
01:21:07,912 --> 01:21:09,846
She cost us a Mohawk son.

985
01:21:09,914 --> 01:21:11,148
BERNIE:
Jake was a big boy.

986
01:21:11,215 --> 01:21:12,683
He knew what
he was doing.

987
01:21:22,993 --> 01:21:24,244
(WHIMPERING)

988
01:21:31,168 --> 01:21:33,069
Jimmy,
get out of here.

989
01:21:47,335 --> 01:21:48,885
You, too.

990
01:21:59,046 --> 01:22:01,498
<i>(CHATTERING ON POLICE RADIO)</i>

991
01:22:18,399 --> 01:22:19,849
I need my half.

992
01:22:23,020 --> 01:22:25,655
No, no, no.
You stay here. Stay here.

993
01:22:35,933 --> 01:22:37,200
Hi, Lila.

994
01:22:39,436 --> 01:22:40,737
Hi, Bernie.

995
01:22:40,805 --> 01:22:42,221
You're in big trouble.

996
01:22:42,289 --> 01:22:44,357
The Council voted
to expel you.

997
01:22:44,424 --> 01:22:46,443
Expel me?
- For five years.

998
01:22:46,510 --> 01:22:48,144
You can appeal,

999
01:22:48,212 --> 01:22:50,029
but I don't think you're going to
be able to change Rosalie's mind.

1000
01:22:50,097 --> 01:22:53,116
I thought all this was legal
on the reservation.

1001
01:22:53,985 --> 01:22:55,284
Look, I got to go.

1002
01:22:55,352 --> 01:22:57,653
BERNIE: If she leaves,
they'll turn you in.

1003
01:22:57,721 --> 01:22:59,939
The troopers
want somebody.

1004
01:23:00,007 --> 01:23:01,341
But she's a Mohawk.

1005
01:23:01,409 --> 01:23:02,959
BERNIE:
The chiefs want her out.

1006
01:23:03,027 --> 01:23:06,262
There's going to be nobody standing
between her and the troopers.

1007
01:23:08,916 --> 01:23:11,651
My kids got no one but me.

1008
01:23:11,719 --> 01:23:14,671
If you leave, she'll
never see her son again.

1009
01:23:14,739 --> 01:23:16,189
Let her go.

1010
01:23:17,475 --> 01:23:18,992
Lila, you're giving
up on him.

1011
01:23:19,060 --> 01:23:20,826
He's only a year old.

1012
01:23:26,100 --> 01:23:27,383
Just go.

1013
01:23:34,258 --> 01:23:37,810
At least you've got family
to take care of him, you know?

1014
01:24:07,542 --> 01:24:08,942
(PANTING)

1015
01:24:39,740 --> 01:24:44,361
I wanted the baby to have a pretty
new crib, not some hand-me-down.

1016
01:24:47,097 --> 01:24:49,232
He wouldn't let me go alone.

1017
01:24:53,103 --> 01:24:57,139
I was too fat to fit
behind the steering wheel.

1018
01:24:57,207 --> 01:25:00,477
BERNIE: He just wanted to
keep you and Little Jake safe.

1019
01:25:00,544 --> 01:25:01,661
(DOOR OPENS)

1020
01:25:05,899 --> 01:25:08,201
Just a couple
of months, right?

1021
01:25:08,268 --> 01:25:10,102
I got no record,
and I'm white.

1022
